5|$|The {{youth leader}} of the troop is the senior <b>patrol</b> <b>leader</b> (SPL), elected by the Scouts in the troop. He is {{responsible}} for the overall performance of the troop, runs troop meetings and ensures that the program for troop meetings and other activities is carried out. He is advised by the Scoutmaster. There may also be one or more assistant senior patrol leaders. Each patrol elects a <b>patrol</b> <b>leader</b> who then appoints an assistant <b>patrol</b> <b>leader</b> and other positions within the patrol. Together, the senior <b>patrol</b> <b>leader,</b> assistant senior <b>patrol</b> <b>leader</b> and patrol leaders make up the patrol leaders council (PLC), the group of Scouts that is responsible for developing the troop's program with the advice of the Scoutmaster.|$|E
